                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">833.6463/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-15T09:00:00-03:30"
                            >July 15, 1941—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>299. Department’s 133, June 25, 7 p.m. Although the substance of the Department’s
                    telegram was conveyed [not?] only to the Minister of Foreign Affairs but orally
                    to Señor Giorgi himself, Giorgi, who had already made plans and who informed
                    Chapin that he had intended to take up other business in the United States, left
                    on the Pan American plane on the 12th via west coast and is proceeding directly
                    to Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
